= Instructions =
* [[OpenDaylight_OpenFlow_Plugin::End_to_End_Inventory|End to End Inventory]]
* [https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/#/c/3314/ Gerrit3314] for controller
<pre>
cd controller
git fetch https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/controller refs/changes/14/3314/9 && git checkout FETCH_HEAD 
mvn clean install</pre>
* [https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/#/c/3451/ Gerrit3451] for openflowplugin
<pre>cd openflowplugin
git fetch https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/openflowplugin refs/changes/51/3451/1 && git checkout FETCH_HEAD 
mvn clean install -nsu</pre>
The -nsu above is critical.  If you don't have it, then the next time the controller artifacts on nexus update they will stomp your local controller build
and things will begin to fail in confusing and mysterious ways.
* Run the local openflowplugin distribution
<pre>cd distribution/base/target/distributions-openflowplugin-base-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT-osgipackage/opendaylight
./run.sh</pre>
* Give it a few seconds to come up :)
* Run mininet with support for OF 1.3 as described in [[OpenDaylight_OpenFlow_Plugin::End_to_End_Inventory|End to End Inventory]]
* Make sure you see the openflow:1 node come up as described in [[OpenDaylight_OpenFlow_Plugin::End_to_End_Inventory|End to End Inventory]]
* With PostMan:
** Set Content-Type to application/yang.data+xml
** Use URL: http://192.168.195.157:8080/restconf/config/opendaylight-inventory:nodes/node/openflow:1/table/0/flow/1
** Use Body:
<pre>
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<flow xmlns="urn:opendaylight:flow:inventory">
    <priority>2</priority>
    <flow-name>Foo</flow-name>
    <match>
        <ethernet-match>
            <ethernet-type>
                <type>2048</type>
            </ethernet-type>
        </ethernet-match>
        <ipv4-destination>10.0.10.2/24</ipv4-destination>
    </match>
    <id>1</id>
    <table_id>0</table_id>
    <instructions>
        <instruction>
            <apply-actions>
                <action>
                    <dec-nw-ttl/>
                </action>
            </apply-actions>
        </instruction>
    </instructions>
</flow>
</pre>
** Note: If you want to try a different flow id or a different table, make sure the URL and the body stay in sync
* See your flow on your mininet:
